President Uhuru Kenyatta confessed to ANC leader Musalia Mudavadi that he was incompetent and wanted the Amani leader to be the Jubilee flagbearer in 2013, Mudavadi has said.Yesterday, he said Uhuru and DP William Ruto later reneged on the agreement.&ldquo;Uhuru told me he wasn&rsquo;t competent to run the government and they wanted me to be the candidate, which indeed has come to pass UhuRuto are incompetent,&rdquo; Mudavadi said.He said the retrenchment in and closure of companies are signs of an ailing economy."We have also seen the abuse of human rights, a vivid sign that the regime is struggling to hold on to power," Mudavadi said.Mudavadi spoke of the events leading to an agreement with Uhuru and Ruto in 2012.&ldquo;Recently I said Jubilee&rsquo;s currency is deceit and their economic model is &lsquo;tenderprocurement&rsquo;. I stand by that statement. The country is so indebted it could be auctioned,&rdquo; the former Deputy PM said.Inflation rate has risen due to incompetent policies of governance executed by Jubilee, he said.&ldquo;Kenya has resources that if well managed will enhance the public sector through the provision of good health, good education and infrastructure,&rdquo; Mudavadi said in a statement.The ANC leader emphasised that NASA's objective is to transform the country&rsquo;s economy and empower individuals and institutions.&ldquo;I have learned the hard way through deceit and backstabbing. I want to see decency restored in our politics. That is why I embarked on the NASA journey even as I was ridiculed and laughed off,&rdquo; he said.Mudavadi said the opposition alliance offers trust as a value in leadership in Kenya, whereas Jubilee leadership has thrived on deceit and dishonesty.&ldquo;Jubilee is a government of procurement. All projects are inflated to give kickbacks,&rdquo; he said.